📘 Topic: What is Docker (Deep Understanding)
💡 Real-World Analogy

Think of Docker like:

👉 Shipping containers in logistics

Every container = same format
Can run anywhere (ship, truck, port)
No dependency issues

👉 Same in Docker:

App + dependencies packaged together
Runs anywhere (your laptop, cloud, server)
🧠 Core Concept
VM vs Container:
Feature	VM	Docker
OS per app	Yes	No
Size	GBs	MBs
Startup time	Minutes	Seconds
Performance	Heavy	Lightweight
⚙️ Docker Architecture (VERY IMPORTANT)

Flow:

docker CLI → Docker Daemon → containerd → runc → Container
Breakdown:
Docker CLI → what you type (docker run)
Docker Daemon → brain (manages everything)
containerd → manages containers lifecycle
runc → actually runs container using Linux features

👉 Internally uses:

Namespaces → isolation
cgroups → resource control
